# 9. Why This Works

The greedy choice is:

> Always make the current element as large as possible while maintaining validity.

Suppose current sequence is

```text
1 2 3
```

Next value is

```text
100
```

Largest valid value is

```text
4
```

Choosing

```text
2
```

instead of

```text
4
```

can never help future elements.

Making an element smaller only reduces future possibilities.

Therefore greedy is always optimal.

